{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0187pyjGaUodmMP6p5WG1xBs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite all remaining Java files","prompt":"I'm migrating a Quarkus coffee shop application to Spring Boot. The project root is at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__quarkus__spring/run_2/output\n\nThe pom.xml has already been updated to Spring Boot 3.2.5, and a CoffeeshopApplication.java main class exists. The domain entities (Order.java, LineItem.java, BaristaItem.java, KitchenOrder.java) have already been migrated to remove PanacheEntity inheritance.\n\nI need you to rewrite the following Java files for Spring Boot. For each file, READ it first, then WRITE the new content:\n\n1. **BaristaRepository.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/barista/domain/BaristaRepository.java)\n   - Was: `implements PanacheRepository<BaristaItem>` with `@ApplicationScoped` and Agroal datasource injection\n   - Should be: Spring Data JPA `extends JpaRepository<BaristaItem, Long>` interface (no class body needed)\n\n2. **KitchenOrderRepository.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/kitchen/domain/KitchenOrderRepository.java)\n   - Was: `implements PanacheRepository<KitchenOrder>` with `@ApplicationScoped` and Agroal datasource injection\n   - Should be: Spring Data JPA `extends JpaRepository<KitchenOrder, Long>` interface\n\n3. **OrderRepository.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/OrderRepository.java)\n   - Was: `implements PanacheRepository<Order>` with `@ApplicationScoped`\n   - Should be: Spring Data JPA `extends JpaRepository<Order, String>` interface with a `findByOrderId(String orderId)` method (since Order uses String orderId as @Id, findById already works, but add findByOrderId as well)\n\n4. **OrderService.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/counter/api/OrderService.java)\n   - Was: interface with methods using Vert.x Message\n   - Should be: simple interface with `void onOrderIn(PlaceOrderCommand placeOrderCommand)` and `void onOrderUp(String message)` (String instead of Message)\n\n5. **OrderServiceImpl.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/counter/OrderServiceImpl.java)\n   - Was: `@ApplicationScoped` with Vert.x EventBus, `@ConsumeEvent`, `@Blocking`\n   - Should be: `@Service` with Spring's `ApplicationEventPublisher` for web updates, and direct method calls.\n   - Replace `eventBus.publish(WEB_UPDATES, ...)` with `applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new WebUpdateEvent(...))`\n   - Replace `eventBus.send(BARISTA_IN, ...)` with `applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new BaristaInEvent(...))`\n   - Replace `eventBus.send(KITCHEN_IN, ...)` with `applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new KitchenInEvent(...))`\n   - Keep `@Transactional` (from jakarta.transaction)\n   - The `onOrderUp` method should take a String (JSON) parameter instead of Message\n\n6. **Barista.java** interface (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/barista/api/Barista.java)\n   - Was: interface with Message parameter\n   - Should be: interface with `void onOrderIn(String orderInJson)`\n\n7. **BaristaImpl.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/barista/BaristaImpl.java)\n   - Was: commented out `@ApplicationScoped` with `@ConsumeEvent`\n   - Keep as-is functionality but don't add Spring annotations since it was commented out in original. Just make it a plain class with no Quarkus imports.\n\n8. **BaristaOutpostImpl.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/barista/BaristaOutpostImpl.java)\n   - Was: `@Startup @ApplicationScoped` with `@ConsumeEvent(BARISTA_IN)` and `@Incoming(\"orders-up\")` for Kafka\n   - Should be: `@Service` with `@EventListener` for BARISTA_IN events, and `@KafkaListener` for orders-up topic\n   - For outgoing Kafka, use `KafkaTemplate<String, String>` instead of SmallRye Emitter\n   - For the `@Incoming(\"orders-up\")` method, use Spring Kafka `@KafkaListener(topics = \"orders-up\")`\n   - Publishing ORDERS_UP events should use `applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new OrdersUpEvent(...))`\n\n9. **Kitchen.java** interface (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/kitchen/Kitchen.java)\n   - Should be: `void onOrderIn(String message)`\n\n10. **KitchenImpl.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/kitchen/KitchenImpl.java)\n    - Was: `@ApplicationScoped` with `@ConsumeEvent(KITCHEN_IN)`, Vert.x EventBus\n    - Should be: `@Service` with `@EventListener` for KitchenInEvent, Spring `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n\n11. **CoffeeshopApiResource.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/web/CoffeeshopApiResource.java)\n    - Was: JAX-RS `@Path(\"/api\")` with `@POST @Path(\"/order\")`\n    - Should be: Spring MVC `@RestController @RequestMapping(\"/api\")` with `@PostMapping(\"/order\")`\n    - Replace `jakarta.ws.rs.*` imports with Spring Web imports\n    - Replace `Response.accepted().build()` with `ResponseEntity.accepted().build()`\n    - For sendMessage endpoint: use `ApplicationEventPublisher` instead of EventBus\n\n12. **DashboardEndpoint.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/web/DashboardEndpoint.java)\n    - Was: JAX-RS SSE with Mutiny Multi and Vert.x EventBus consumer\n    - Should be: Spring SSE with `SseEmitter`. Create a `@RestController` with `@GetMapping(\"/dashboard/stream\")` that returns `SseEmitter`. Keep a list of active emitters and send events to them.\n\n13. **WebResource.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/web/WebResource.java)\n    - Was: Qute template with `@ConfigProperty`\n    - Should be: Spring MVC `@Controller` with `@Value` annotations and Thymeleaf `Model`\n    - Return a string template name \"coffeeshopTemplate\" and populate model attributes\n\n14. **EventBusTopics.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/EventBusTopics.java)\n    - Keep as-is (it's just constants)\n\n15. **JsonUtil.java** (src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/utils/JsonUtil.java)\n    - Keep as-is (no Quarkus-specific code)\n\nYou also need to CREATE these new event classes for Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher pattern:\n\n16. **Create WebUpdateEvent.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/events/WebUpdateEvent.java\n    - Simple class with `String payload` field, constructor, getter\n\n17. **Create BaristaInEvent.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/events/BaristaInEvent.java\n    - Simple class with `String payload` field, constructor, getter\n\n18. **Create KitchenInEvent.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/events/KitchenInEvent.java\n    - Simple class with `String payload` field, constructor, getter\n\n19. **Create OrdersUpEvent.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/events/OrdersUpEvent.java\n    - Simple class with `String payload` field, constructor, getter\n\nFor the DashboardEndpoint, you need a mechanism to push SSE updates. Create a DashboardService:\n\n20. **Create DashboardService.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/web/DashboardService.java\n    - `@Service` class\n    - Has `@EventListener` for `WebUpdateEvent` \n    - Maintains a `CopyOnWriteArrayList<SseEmitter>` \n    - When a WebUpdateEvent arrives, send it to all active emitters\n    - Provides `registerEmitter(SseEmitter emitter)` method\n\nFor the Kafka configuration, since Kafka might not be available when running standalone, make it optional:\n\n21. **Create KafkaConfig.java** at src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/infrastructure/KafkaConfig.java\n    - `@Configuration` with `@ConditionalOnProperty(name = \"spring.kafka.bootstrap-servers\")`\n    - Just an empty config marker class\n\nIMPORTANT: For each file, you MUST read it first then write. The BaristaOutpostImpl should gracefully handle if Kafka is not available. Use `@KafkaListener` with `autoStartup = \"${kafka.enabled:false}\"` so it doesn't crash without Kafka.\n\nPlease process ALL files above. Read each existing file then write the new version.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9921,"cache_read_input_tokens":108110,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9921,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2638},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"0a607070-cc0f-4ce1-a175-6ea43b102394"}
