{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015zGppRKWQdK4JJehzj8gRZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands.PlaceOrderCommand;\n     6→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n     7→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     8→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     9→\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    11→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/api\")\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    22→public class CoffeeshopApiResource {\n    23→\n    24→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(CoffeeshopApiResource.class);\n    25→\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    OrderService orderService;\n    28→\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    EventBus eventBus;\n    31→\n    32→    @POST\n    33→    @Path(\"/order\")\n    34→    @Transactional\n    35→    public Response placeOrder(final PlaceOrderCommand placeOrderCommand) {\n    36→\n    37→        LOGGER.info(\"PlaceOrderCommand received: {}\", placeOrderCommand);\n    38→        orderService.onOrderIn(placeOrderCommand);\n    39→        return Response.accepted().build();\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    @POST\n    43→    @Path(\"/message\")\n    44→    public void sendMessage(final String message) {\n    45→//        webUpdater.send(message);\n    46→        LOGGER.debug(\"received message: {}\", message);\n    47→        LOGGER.debug(\"sending to web-updates: {}\", message);\n    48→        eventBus.publish(\"web-updates\", message);\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"49d618db-1c8e-4314-89b9-c7a3c927076e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NMs6UL9BXdgtykkGE8X98X","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→import io.smallrye.mutiny.Multi;\n     4→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n     5→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n     6→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     7→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     8→\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→\n    15→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.WEB_UPDATES;\n    16→\n    17→@Path(\"/dashboard\")\n    18→public class DashboardEndpoint {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(DashboardEndpoint.class);\n    21→\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    EventBus eventBus;\n    24→\n    25→    @GET\n    26→    @Path(\"/stream\")\n    27→    @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    28→    public Multi<String> dashboardStream() {\n    29→\n    30→        return eventBus.<String>consumer(WEB_UPDATES)\n    31→                .toMulti()\n    32→                .map(Message::body);\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"fe46b935-9b3f-47a0-85eb-9162b3ac34f9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017C5xSA2nsMKjtHWPUwRDAg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    13→\n    14→@Path(\"/\")\n    15→public class WebResource {\n    16→\n    17→    @ConfigProperty(name=\"streamUrl\")\n    18→    String streamUrl;\n    19→\n    20→    @ConfigProperty(name=\"storeId\")\n    21→    String storeId;\n    22→\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    OrderService orderService;\n    25→\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    Template coffeeshopTemplate;\n    28→\n    29→    @GET\n    30→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    31→    public TemplateInstance getIndex(){\n    32→\n    33→        return coffeeshopTemplate\n    34→                .data(\"streamUrl\", streamUrl)\n    35→                .data(\"storeId\", storeId);\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"62238d13-4a6f-40a8-8378-8073304e5bf8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017DSZ5qwgAcaziNyLPfCznM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure;\n     2→\n     3→public class EventBusTopics {\n     4→\n     5→    public static final String WEB_UPDATES = \"web-updates\";\n     6→    public static final String BARISTA_IN = \"barista-in\";\n     7→    public static final String KITCHEN_IN = \"kitchen-in\";\n     8→    public static final String ORDERS_UP = \"orders-up\";\n     9→\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"50ca6f72-d5a5-42ca-b309-bedc9b8d4258"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D4wjZ3wypwo7ghkNi1NPtk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jdk8.Jdk8Module;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     9→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    10→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    11→\n    12→public class JsonUtil {\n    13→\n    14→    private static Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(JsonUtil.class);\n    15→\n    16→    private static final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper()\n    17→            .registerModules(new JavaTimeModule(),new Jdk8Module());\n    18→\n    19→    public static String toJson(final Object object) {\n    20→        LOGGER.debug(\"marshalling {} to JSON\", object.toString());\n    21→        try {\n    22→            return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(object);\n    23→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    24→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    25→            return \"{ \\\"error\\\" : \\\"\" + e.getMessage() + \"\\\" }\";\n    26→        }\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public static <T> T fromJson(final String json, Class clazz) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            return (T) objectMapper.readValue(json, clazz);\n    32→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    33→            e.printStackTrace();\n    34→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    35→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    36→        }\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static OrderUp fromJsonToOrderUp(String json) {\n    40→        try {\n    41→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderUp.class);\n    42→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    43→            e.printStackTrace();\n    44→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    45→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    46→        }\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static OrderIn fromJsonToOrderIn(String json) {\n    50→        try {\n    51→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderIn.class);\n    52→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    53→            e.printStackTrace();\n    54→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    55→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    56→        }\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XVC1ogVPPPmAEN3mjFzkCZ","session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"935b3443-4fa8-4484-afe1-0a1011361ec0"}
