{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GBBMHAWnydHKf88YqeTBKt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain.BaristaItem;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain.BaristaRepository;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils.JsonUtil;\n     9→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    10→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    11→\n    12→import java.time.Instant;\n    13→\n    14→public class BaristaImpl {\n    15→\n    16→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(BaristaImpl.class);\n    17→\n    18→    private final String madeBy = \"Mr. Spock\";\n    19→\n    20→    private BaristaRepository baristaRepository;\n    21→\n    22→    public void onOrderIn(final String message) {\n    23→        OrderIn orderIn = JsonUtil.fromJson(message, OrderIn.class);\n    24→        BaristaItem baristaItem = new BaristaItem();\n    25→        baristaItem.setItem(orderIn.item.toString());\n    26→        baristaItem.setTimeIn(Instant.now());\n    27→        LOGGER.debug(\"order in : {}\", orderIn);\n    28→        try {\n    29→            Thread.sleep(calculateDelay(orderIn.item));\n    30→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    31→            e.printStackTrace();\n    32→        }\n    33→        OrderUp orderUp = new OrderUp(\n    34→                orderIn.orderId,\n    35→                orderIn.itemId,\n    36→                orderIn.item,\n    37→                orderIn.name,\n    38→                Instant.now(),\n    39→                madeBy);\n    40→        baristaItem.setTimeUp(Instant.now());\n    41→        baristaRepository.save(baristaItem);\n    42→        // Note: Would need event bus to publish ORDERS_UP\n    43→        LOGGER.debug(\"OrderUp: {}\", JsonUtil.toJson(orderUp));\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    private int calculateDelay(final Item item) {\n    47→        switch (item) {\n    48→            case COFFEE_BLACK:\n    49→                return 5000;\n    50→            case COFFEE_WITH_ROOM:\n    51→                return 5000;\n    52→            case ESPRESSO:\n    53→                return 7000;\n    54→            case ESPRESSO_DOUBLE:\n    55→                return 7000;\n    56→            case CAPPUCCINO:\n    57→                return 10000;\n    58→            default:\n    59→                return 3000;\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→}\n    64→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"fda08002-5386-4d77-82ba-73ba8a4a879d"}
