{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018jn31HucVBFWYppU9jskH8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Location;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.OrderSource;\n     8→\n     9→import java.time.Instant;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.Optional;\n    12→\n    13→public class PlaceOrderCommand {\n    14→\n    15→    private final CommandType commandType = CommandType.PLACE_ORDER;\n    16→\n    17→    private final String id;\n    18→\n    19→    private final OrderSource orderSource;\n    20→\n    21→    private final Location location;\n    22→\n    23→    private final String loyaltyMemberId;\n    24→\n    25→    private final List<CommandItem> baristaItems;\n    26→\n    27→    private final List<CommandItem> kitchenItems;\n    28→\n    29→    private final Instant timestamp;\n    30→\n    31→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    32→    public PlaceOrderCommand(\n    33→            @JsonProperty(\"id\") final String id,\n    34→            @JsonProperty(\"orderSource\") final OrderSource orderSource,\n    35→            @JsonProperty(\"storeId\") final Location location,\n    36→            @JsonProperty(\"rewardsId\") final Optional<String> loyaltyMemberId,\n    37→            @JsonProperty(\"baristaItems\") Optional<List<CommandItem>> baristaItems,\n    38→            @JsonProperty(\"kitchenItems\") Optional<List<CommandItem>> kitchenItems,\n    39→            @JsonProperty(\"commandType\") final CommandType commandType) {\n    40→        this.id = id;\n    41→        this.orderSource = orderSource;\n    42→        this.location = location;\n    43→        if (loyaltyMemberId.isPresent()) {\n    44→            this.loyaltyMemberId = loyaltyMemberId.get();\n    45→        }else{\n    46→            this.loyaltyMemberId = null;\n    47→        }\n    48→        if (baristaItems.isPresent()) {\n    49→            this.baristaItems = baristaItems.get();\n    50→        }else{\n    51→            this.baristaItems = null;\n    52→        }\n    53→        if (kitchenItems.isPresent()) {\n    54→            this.kitchenItems = kitchenItems.get();\n    55→        }else{\n    56→            this.kitchenItems = null;\n    57→        }\n    58→        this.timestamp = Instant.now();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public String toString() {\n    63→        return \"PlaceOrderCommand{\" +\n    64→                \"id='\" + id + '\\'' +\n    65→                \", orderSource=\" + orderSource +\n    66→                \", location=\" + location +\n    67→                \", loyaltyMemberId='\" + loyaltyMemberId + '\\'' +\n    68→                \", baristaItems=\" + baristaItems +\n    69→                \", kitchenItems=\" + kitchenItems +\n    70→                \", timestamp=\" + timestamp +\n    71→                '}';\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    @Override\n    75→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    76→        if (this == o) return true;\n    77→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    78→\n    79→        PlaceOrderCommand that = (PlaceOrderCommand) o;\n    80→\n    81→        if (id != null ? !id.equals(that.id) : that.id != null) return false;\n    82→        if (orderSource != that.orderSource) return false;\n    83→        if (location != that.location) return false;\n    84→        if (loyaltyMemberId != null ? !loyaltyMemberId.equals(that.loyaltyMemberId) : that.loyaltyMemberId != null)\n    85→            return false;\n    86→        if (baristaItems != null ? !baristaItems.equals(that.baristaItems) : that.baristaItems != null)\n    87→            return false;\n    88→        if (kitchenItems != null ? !kitchenItems.equals(that.kitchenItems) : that.kitchenItems != null)\n    89→            return false;\n    90→        return timestamp != null ? timestamp.equals(that.timestamp) : that.timestamp == null;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    @Override\n    94→    public int hashCode() {\n    95→        int result = id != null ? id.hashCode() : 0;\n    96→        result = 31 * result + (orderSource != null ? orderSource.hashCode() : 0);\n    97→        result = 31 * result + (location != null ? location.hashCode() : 0);\n    98→        result = 31 * result + (loyaltyMemberId != null ? loyaltyMemberId.hashCode() : 0);\n    99→        result = 31 * result + (baristaItems != null ? baristaItems.hashCode() : 0);\n   100→        result = 31 * result + (kitchenItems != null ? kitchenItems.hashCode() : 0);\n   101→        result = 31 * result + (timestamp != null ? timestamp.hashCode() : 0);\n   102→        return result;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    public Optional<List<CommandItem>> getBaristaItems() {\n   106→        return Optional.ofNullable(baristaItems);\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public Optional<List<CommandItem>> getKitchenItems() {\n   110→        return Optional.ofNullable(kitchenItems);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    public Optional<String> getLoyaltyMemberId() {\n   114→        return Optional.ofNullable(loyaltyMemberId);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public String getId() {\n   118→        return id;\n   119→    }\n   120→\n   121→    public OrderSource getOrderSource() {\n   122→        return orderSource;\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    public Location getLocation() {\n   126→        return location;\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    public Instant getTimestamp() {\n   130→        return timestamp;\n   131→    }\n   132→}\n   133→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"789db259-c925-44c5-84a3-f608c52b5579"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CUMYCrc3DCEYmNoF42Cskd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     5→\n     6→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n     7→import java.util.StringJoiner;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Representst the individual line items in a PlaceOrderCommand\n    11→ */\n    12→public class CommandItem {\n    13→\n    14→    public final Item item;\n    15→\n    16→    public final String name;\n    17→\n    18→    public final BigDecimal price;\n    19→\n    20→    public CommandItem(\n    21→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    22→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name,\n    23→            @JsonProperty(\"price\") BigDecimal price) {\n    24→        this.item = item;\n    25→        this.name = name;\n    26→        this.price = price;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    @Override\n    30→    public String toString() {\n    31→        return new StringJoiner(\", \", CommandItem.class.getSimpleName() + \"[\", \"]\")\n    32→                .add(\"item=\" + item)\n    33→                .add(\"name='\" + name + \"'\")\n    34→                .add(\"price=\" + price)\n    35→                .toString();\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    40→        if (this == o) return true;\n    41→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    42→\n    43→        CommandItem that = (CommandItem) o;\n    44→\n    45→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    46→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    47→        return price != null ? price.equals(that.price) : that.price == null;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public int hashCode() {\n    52→        int result = item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0;\n    53→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    54→        result = 31 * result + (price != null ? price.hashCode() : 0);\n    55→        return result;\n    56→    }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"c23f942e-22f2-4a7c-8280-07342990d0de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017e5hDF811i9EtddNjQCj46","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * A value object encapsulating the information sent to Barista and Kitchen\n    11→ */\n    12→public class OrderIn {\n    13→\n    14→    public final String orderId;\n    15→\n    16→    public final String itemId;\n    17→\n    18→    public final Item item;\n    19→\n    20→    public final String name;\n    21→\n    22→    public final Instant timeIn;\n    23→\n    24→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    25→    public OrderIn(\n    26→            @JsonProperty(\"orderId\") String orderId,\n    27→            @JsonProperty(\"lineItemId\") String itemId,\n    28→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    29→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name) {\n    30→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    31→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    32→        this.item = item;\n    33→        this.name = name;\n    34→        this.timeIn = Instant.now();\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public String toString() {\n    39→        return \"OrderTicket{\" +\n    40→                \"orderId='\" + orderId + '\\'' +\n    41→                \", lineItemId='\" + itemId + '\\'' +\n    42→                \", item=\" + item +\n    43→                \", name='\" + name + '\\'' +\n    44→                \", timestamp=\" + timeIn +\n    45→                '}';\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    50→        if (this == o) return true;\n    51→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    52→\n    53→        OrderIn that = (OrderIn) o;\n    54→\n    55→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    56→        if (itemId != null ? !itemId.equals(that.itemId) : that.itemId != null) return false;\n    57→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    58→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    59→        return timeIn != null ? timeIn.equals(that.timeIn) : that.timeIn == null;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @Override\n    63→    public int hashCode() {\n    64→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    65→        result = 31 * result + (itemId != null ? itemId.hashCode() : 0);\n    66→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    67→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    68→        result = 31 * result + (timeIn != null ? timeIn.hashCode() : 0);\n    69→        return result;\n    70→    }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"3da38c36-3b22-4ebd-a82c-fcba6b2b6602"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TMvmVXNT6hGGQEUsyZyafu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→public class OrderUp extends OrderIn{\n    10→\n    11→    public final String madeBy;\n    12→\n    13→    public final Instant timeUp;\n    14→\n    15→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    16→    public OrderUp(\n    17→            @JsonProperty(\"orderId\") String orderId,\n    18→            @JsonProperty(\"lineItemId\") String lineItemId,\n    19→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    20→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name,\n    21→            @JsonProperty(\"timestamp\") Instant timeUp,\n    22→            @JsonProperty(\"madeBy\") String madeBy) {\n    23→        super(orderId, lineItemId, item, name);\n    24→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n    25→        this.madeBy = madeBy;\n    26→    }\n    27→\n    28→    @Override\n    29→    public String toString() {\n    30→        return \"OrderUp{\" +\n    31→                \"orderId='\" + orderId + '\\'' +\n    32→                \", lineItemId='\" + itemId + '\\'' +\n    33→                \", item=\" + item +\n    34→                \", name='\" + name + '\\'' +\n    35→                \", timestamp=\" + timeUp +\n    36→                \", madeBy='\" + madeBy + '\\'' +\n    37→                '}';\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Override\n    41→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    42→\n    43→        if (this == o) return true;\n    44→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    45→        if (!super.equals(o)) return false;\n    46→\n    47→        OrderUp orderUp = (OrderUp) o;\n    48→\n    49→        return madeBy != null ? madeBy.equals(orderUp.madeBy) : orderUp.madeBy == null;\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public int hashCode() {\n    54→        int result = super.hashCode();\n    55→        result = 31 * result + (madeBy != null ? madeBy.hashCode() : 0);\n    56→        return result;\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"abee980f-a198-4272-aaed-aa17fbe21381"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012E46pCy3Hz2koKUx9h2XdP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.OrderStatus;\n     5→\n     6→public class OrderUpdate {\n     7→\n     8→    public final String orderId;\n     9→\n    10→    public final String itemId;\n    11→\n    12→    public final String name;\n    13→\n    14→    public final Item item;\n    15→\n    16→    public final OrderStatus status;\n    17→\n    18→    public final String madeBy;\n    19→\n    20→    public OrderUpdate(final String orderId, final String itemId, final String name, final Item item, final OrderStatus status) {\n    21→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    22→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    23→        this.name = name;\n    24→        this.item = item;\n    25→        this.status = status;\n    26→        this.madeBy = null;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public OrderUpdate(final String orderId, final String itemId, final String name, final Item item, final OrderStatus status, final String madeBy) {\n    30→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    31→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    32→        this.name = name;\n    33→        this.item = item;\n    34→        this.status = status;\n    35→        this.madeBy = madeBy;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public String toString() {\n    40→        final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(\"OrderUpdate{\");\n    41→        sb.append(\"orderId='\").append(orderId).append('\\'');\n    42→        sb.append(\", itemId='\").append(itemId).append('\\'');\n    43→        sb.append(\", name='\").append(name).append('\\'');\n    44→        sb.append(\", item=\").append(item);\n    45→        sb.append(\", status=\").append(status);\n    46→        sb.append(\", madeBy='\").append(madeBy).append('\\'');\n    47→        sb.append('}');\n    48→        return sb.toString();\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    53→        if (this == o) return true;\n    54→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    55→\n    56→        OrderUpdate that = (OrderUpdate) o;\n    57→\n    58→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    59→        if (itemId != null ? !itemId.equals(that.itemId) : that.itemId != null) return false;\n    60→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    61→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    62→        if (status != that.status) return false;\n    63→        return madeBy != null ? madeBy.equals(that.madeBy) : that.madeBy == null;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public int hashCode() {\n    68→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    69→        result = 31 * result + (itemId != null ? itemId.hashCode() : 0);\n    70→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    71→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    72→        result = 31 * result + (status != null ? status.hashCode() : 0);\n    73→        result = 31 * result + (madeBy != null ? madeBy.hashCode() : 0);\n    74→        return result;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→\n    78→}\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"7fbd2113-a224-4eec-bd77-381954207119"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011R4wqnZGDNhS689crq7GzP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jdk8.Jdk8Module;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     9→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    10→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    11→\n    12→public class JsonUtil {\n    13→\n    14→    private static Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(JsonUtil.class);\n    15→\n    16→    private static final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper()\n    17→            .registerModules(new JavaTimeModule(),new Jdk8Module());\n    18→\n    19→    public static String toJson(final Object object) {\n    20→        LOGGER.debug(\"marshalling {} to JSON\", object.toString());\n    21→        try {\n    22→            return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(object);\n    23→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    24→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    25→            return \"{ \\\"error\\\" : \\\"\" + e.getMessage() + \"\\\" }\";\n    26→        }\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public static <T> T fromJson(final String json, Class clazz) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            return (T) objectMapper.readValue(json, clazz);\n    32→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    33→            e.printStackTrace();\n    34→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    35→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    36→        }\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static OrderUp fromJsonToOrderUp(String json) {\n    40→        try {\n    41→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderUp.class);\n    42→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    43→            e.printStackTrace();\n    44→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    45→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    46→        }\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static OrderIn fromJsonToOrderIn(String json) {\n    50→        try {\n    51→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderIn.class);\n    52→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    53→            e.printStackTrace();\n    54→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    55→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    56→        }\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a1c50a88-828f-43a6-8dbe-524f630482b2","uuid":"aa01a851-f771-4f3b-b162-bd88dcc85be9"}
